{
  "texts": [
    "Connecting regularity to the Flat Chain Conjecture and further discussionThe fact that there is some connection between metric currents and Jacobians is not deep, as it can be immediately seen from [30,Theorem 5.5], nor new.",
    "The first instance where this is explored seems to be due to De Lellis [18], where a theory of Jacobians is developed in a metric space using the theory of metric currents.",
    "Our observations, however, link Jacobians to metric currents closely enough to allow us to obtain invalidity of Lang's Flat Chain Conjecture.",
    "The most precise statement we are able to make about this connection is Theorem 3.18, special case of which follows.",
    "The proof of Theorem 1.6 is non-constructive, as it relies on the open mapping theorem."
  ]
}